2 (f) Any justice of the supreme court, chancery court
3 judge or district court judge of this state, who has
4 retired pursuant to the provisions of this section, and who
5 is not practicing law, may, notwithstanding his retirement,
6 be called upon, with his consent, at the request of a
7 district court judge or circuit court judge, with the
8 consent of the chief justice, or by the chief justice, and
9 assigned to service on any court. A retired justice or
10 judge shall receive as a salary during any period of
11 assignment an amount equal to the current compensation of a
12 judge of the court to which he is assigned. The salary
13 received by a retired justice or judge during any period of
14 assignment shall not affect the receipt of any retirement
15 allowance received by the retired justice or judge during
16 the period of assignment. Assignments of retired justices
17 or judges under this section shall only be made in a manner
18 that does not jeopardize the qualified status of state
19 retirement plans established by the Wyoming legislature.
